President Obama issued a statement praising Senator Daniel Akaka for his lifetime of service. Akaka served in the Army Corps of Engineers during World War II and later became an educator before entering politics. He spent over three decades in Congress, where he focused on issues such as the well-being of troops, veterans, and Native Hawaiians, as well as reforming Wall Street and advocating for fair treatment of consumers and small business owners. President Obama expressed his gratitude to Akaka for his dedication and wished him the best for the future.